text.__SUMMARY__:
Wahlenbergia densifolia, commonly known as the fairy bluebell, is a small herbaceous plant in the family Campanulaceae native to eastern Australia.
The erect perennial herb typically grows to a height of 0.07 to 0.3 metres (0 to 1 ft). It blooms in the summer between October and February producing blue-purple flowers.The species is found in New South Wales and Victoria.
